1. install tavern and pytest:
    pip install tavern, pytest
2. build orchestrator-agent (use ./build.sh)    
3. create vagrant boxes for test (see Vagrantfile for options):
    vagrant --mysql-version=57 --mysql-replication=gtid --orchagent-config=backupolddatadir up
4. run ./updateTokens.sh
5. save snapshot if you plan to run different tests with current VM setup:
    vagrant snapshot save orch-agent1
6. start test:
    a) common tests (use files located in conf/common/ and test_common.tavern.yaml to run different tests):
        PYTHONPATH=$(pwd) tavern-ci --stdout --tavern-global-cfg common.yaml conf/common/mydumper_full.yaml -- test_common.tavern.yaml
    b) stream tests (use files located in conf/stream/ and test_stream.tavern.yaml to run different tests):
        PYTHONPATH=$(pwd) tavern-ci --stdout --tavern-global-cfg common.yaml conf/stream/xtrabackup_stream_partial_backupdir.yaml -- test_stream.tavern.yaml
7. run ./check.sh to verify replication
8. restore snapshot if you want to run different test with current VM setup:
    vagrant snapshot restore orch-agent1
9. destroy vagrant VMs:
    vagrant --mysql-version=57 --mysql-replication=gtid --orchagent-config=backupolddatadir destroy